history.content: No, you'd be considered a Junior unfortunately, and would not have any reserved seats to avail.

If I am a rising junior (undeclared), would I be considered an undeclared sophomore student during my phase 1? I am trying to take 61b next semester, but there are no seats reserved for undeclared L&S juniors:

48  Seats Reserved for Electrical Engineering & Computer Science, EECS/Materials Science & Engineering, and EECS/Nuclear Engineering Majors; and Undeclared Students in the College of Engineering
608  Seats Reserved for College of Letters & Sciences: Undeclared Freshman and Sophomore Students or Transfer Students
history.subject: Rising junior interested in taking 61b. can I even enroll?
